  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2022 Syria Regional Appeal - Syria - Emergency Repair and Maintenance of UNRWA Installations</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contrary to the principle of the inviolability of United Nations premises, UNRWA facilities in Syria have suffered extensive damage throughout the conflict. Many Palestine refugee camps have seen major hostilities, particularly Ein el Tal (Aleppo), Dera&#x2019;a (South) and Yarmouk (Damascus) official and non-official camps, which have sustained large-scale destruction. 

In 2021, UNRWA will continue to focus on resuming its core services in areas where access has resumed and civilians are spontaneously returning. The Agency&#x2019;s priority is to ensure safe and secured access to its education and health facilities and to support the restoration of basic WASH services, such as water and sewage connections.</narrative>
  </description>
